# Language Standard — English (en-US) Default

## Rule

**The default language of the project is English (en-US). All project content must be in English.**

This applies to:
- **Code**: file names, directory names, variables, functions, classes, interfaces, types, enums, constants, route paths, query params, DTOs, env vars, test descriptions (`describe`, `it`, `test`), comments, JSDoc
- **Cursor rules**: `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` — titles, descriptions, and body text in English
- **Documentation**: all `*.md` files (README, TODO, CONTRIBUTING, etc.) in English
- **Commits**: subject and body in English (Conventional Commits)
- **User-facing messages**: CLI output, error messages, and prompts in English

## No Exceptions

There are **no** language exceptions for project content. The project is not restricted to Portuguese speakers; everything is in English so that any contributor or user can understand and contribute.

## Examples

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG – non-English names in code
class FaturaEntity {
  constructor(public readonly numeroCliente: string) {}
}

// ✅ CORRECT – English names in code
class InvoiceEntity {
  constructor(public readonly customerNumber: string) {}
}
```

```
// ❌ WRONG – non-English route paths
GET /api/v1/faturas?numero_cliente=123

// ✅ CORRECT – English route paths
GET /api/v1/invoices?customer_number=123
```
